title.narrative: OUTPUT 2.1: ENROLMENT AND RETENTION ECD, PRIMARY AND SECONDARY

description.narrative: Output 2.1: Increased enrolment and retention of girls and boys in pre-primary, primary and secondary education, particularly in the ASAL counties and informal settlements, targeting parents, teachers, communities and other partners to support children, which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 2 - Improved Early Learning and Education: An increased proportion of children aged 0 to 18, especially girls from most disadvantaged counties, informal settlements and those affected by humanitarian crisis, access quality, gender- sensitive ECD and education services, with increased transition to secondary education.

title.narrative: Output 2.1: Increased enrolment and retention of girls and boys in pre-primary, primary and secondary education, particularly in the ASAL counties and informal settlements, targeting parents, teachers, communities and other partners to support children

description.narrative: During the year, UNICEF has contributed to reducing the number of Out Of School Children by 31,247 children (48 per cent girls and 1.4 per cent children with disabilities) in 9 ASAL counties and 2 informal settlements through a package of multisectoral and disability-sensitive interventions that include capacity building of teachers and Board of Management (BoM), WASH facilities, child protection interventions, sports for development and disability assessment. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
